@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor white
title D5: Simultaneous Crash + Byzantine\n(Core Project 2 Scenario: 1 crash + 1 Byzantine at same time)

actor "Client" as C
participant "FE" as FE #E3F2FD
participant "Sequencer" as SEQ #FFF8E1
participant "R1\n(correct)" as R1 #E8F5E9
participant "R2\n**CRASHED**" as R2 #FFD0D0
participant "R3\n**Byzantine**" as R3 #FFD0D0
participant "R4\n(correct)" as R4 #E8F5E9
participant "All RMs" as RM #FFECB3

== Dual Fault: R2 killed, R3 returns random ==

C -> FE : SOAP request
FE -> SEQ : REQUEST
SEQ -> R1 : EXECUTE(s_g)
SEQ -> R2 : EXECUTE(s_g)
SEQ -> R3 : EXECUTE(s_g)
SEQ -> R4 : EXECUTE(s_g)

R1 -> FE : RESULT: "SUCCESS"
R4 -> FE : RESULT: "SUCCESS"

note over FE #C8E6C9
  **f+1 = 2 identical (R1 + R4)**
  Correct result returned immediately
  System works despite dual fault!
end note

FE --> C : "SUCCESS"

R3 -> FE : RESULT: "WRONG_DATA"
note over FE : R3 differs from majority\nbyzantineCount[R3]++
FE -> RM : INCORRECT_RESULT(R3)

note over FE #FFCCCC
  Timeout expired: R2 never responded
end note
FE -> RM : CRASH_SUSPECT(R2)

note over FE, RM
  **Key: from 4 replicas, 3 respond (R2 crashed).**
  **Of 3 responses, 1 is Byzantine (R3).**
  **2 correct (R1, R4) still provide f+1=2 match.**
end note

== Parallel Recovery ==

RM -> RM : VOTE: R2 crashed (majority confirms)
RM -> R1 : STATE_REQUEST
R1 -> RM : STATE_TRANSFER

RM -> R2 : Launch new R2
RM -> R2 : INIT_STATE
R2 -> SEQ : READY
SEQ -> R2 : Replay missed
note over R2 #E8F5E9 : R2 recovered

== Byzantine Threshold (after 3 consecutive) ==

note over FE : After 3 consecutive incorrect\nfrom R3: REPLACE_REQUEST
FE -> RM : REPLACE_REQUEST(R3, BYZANTINE)
RM -> RM : Vote: majority agrees
RM -> R3 : SHUTDOWN
RM -> R1 : STATE_REQUEST
R1 -> RM : STATE_TRANSFER

RM -> R3 : Launch new R3
RM -> R3 : INIT_STATE
R3 -> SEQ : READY
SEQ -> R3 : Replay missed
note over R3 #E8F5E9 : R3 replaced

note over R1, R4 #C8E6C9
  **System fully restored: 4 healthy replicas**
end note
@enduml
